# .env.staging.example
#
# Template for staging-environment secrets (Neon free tier, Frankfurt).
# Copy to .env.staging and fill in real values:
#
#   cp .env.staging.example .env.staging && chmod 600 .env.staging && $EDITOR .env.staging
#
# .env.staging is gitignored (see .gitignore: .env.staging) — it will NEVER
# be committed. Only this template (.env.staging.example) is committed.
#
# Per ADR-011, staging secrets are stored in .env.staging (NOT in Doppler)
# because Doppler Service Tokens require the Team plan (~$99/mo) and the
# project is on the free Developer plan. CI (Phase 7) will use GitHub
# Actions encrypted secrets for the same values — see ADR-011 Tier 2.
#
# SECURITY: Never paste real secrets into this file. This file is a TEMPLATE
# committed to a PUBLIC repo. Real values go in .env.staging only.
# If you accidentally commit a real secret, rotate it immediately and
# follow docs/runbooks/breach-response.md.
#
# How to populate (operator or AI-agent sandbox):
#   1. As neondb_owner on Neon, run:
#        ALTER ROLE ops_superuser WITH LOGIN PASSWORD '<strong_pw>' BYPASSRLS;
#        ALTER ROLE app_role    WITH LOGIN PASSWORD '<strong_pw>' NOBYPASSRLS;
#      (Generate strong passwords via: openssl rand -base64 24)
#   2. Fill in DATABASE_URL with the app_role connection string (new password).
#   3. MIGRATION_DATABASE_URL and DIRECT_URL_STAGING use the neondb_owner
#      connection string (per JC-18-5 — Neon restricts role privileges;
#      only neondb_owner has CREATE on the public schema).
#   4. chmod 600 .env.staging
#   5. Verify: set -a && . ./.env.staging && set +a && \
#        pnpm --filter @clinic-saas/db test
#      All 19 tests should pass.

# =============================================================================
# Neon staging connection strings (per ADR-011 Tier 1 + JC-18-5)
# =============================================================================

# DATABASE_URL — the app connection. Connects as app_role (NOBYPASSRLS),
# so RLS policies are enforced on every query. Used by apps/api,
# apps/worker, apps/web at runtime in staging.
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://app_role:APP_ROLE_PASSWORD_HERE@ep-holy-glade-asqt1jwl.c-4.eu-central-1.aws.neon.tech/neondb?sslmode=require

# MIGRATION_DATABASE_URL — the migration connection. Connects as
# neondb_owner (BYPASSRLS) per JC-18-5. Used by: pnpm db:migrate,
# pnpm db:seed. The drizzle.config.ts reads this var (falling back to
# DATABASE_URL if unset).
MIGRATION_DATABASE_URL=postgresql://neondb_owner:NEONDB_OWNER_PASSWORD_HERE@ep-holy-glade-asqt1jwl.c-4.eu-central-1.aws.neon.tech/neondb?sslmode=require

# DIRECT_URL_STAGING — the Neon owner connection (neondb_owner, BYPASSRLS).
# Used for admin operations (creating/dropping roles, extension management,
# FORCE RLS re-application, audit-log immutability re-application).
DIRECT_URL_STAGING=postgresql://neondb_owner:NEONDB_OWNER_PASSWORD_HERE@ep-holy-glade-asqt1jwl.c-4.eu-central-1.aws.neon.tech/neondb?sslmode=require

# =============================================================================
# How to load these into your shell (for local pnpm invocations)
# =============================================================================
#   set -a && . ./.env.staging && set +a
#   pnpm --filter @clinic-saas/db test
#
# Or, for a single command:
#   env $(grep -v '^#' .env.staging | xargs) pnpm --filter @clinic-saas/db test
#
# CI (Phase 7) will load these from GitHub Actions encrypted secrets instead
# — see ADR-011 Tier 2 and docs/runbooks/ci-secrets.md (to be written in
# Phase 7).

# =============================================================================
# Production is NOT here
# =============================================================================
# Per Blueprint §3 and Law 18-07: patient-identifiable health data must
# reside in Algeria. Neon (Frankfurt) is acceptable for STAGING (no real
# patient data) but NOT for production. Production uses CERIST Cloud or
# Djezzy Cloud VPS, configured in Phase 16 per ADR-011 Tier 3.
